Presentation

Moreover, you will have the opportunity to get key insights on brand management and how our passionate Talents build the long-term success of our Maisons.

Discover Brand Management at Parfums Christian Dior

Parfums Christian Dior and the Future of Beauty

The world is constantly evolving, and the Covid-19 pandemic has been an accelerator of trends. What is the future of marketing and brand management at Parfums Christian Dior? And how can Parfums Christian Dior ensure it continues to connect with consumers? Claudia Marcocci shares her thoughts on this and more.

 

Claudia, what is your vision of brand management today and its future? And especially at Parfums Christian Dior?

 

When we talk about the future, you need to know that over the last few years, the role of marketers has changed dramatically. When I started, it was about selling the ‘product’ via the ‘make-believe’. Today, it’s above all finding the perfect balance between a “product and client centric approach”. Consumers have more than ever turned into powerful purchase decision makers, however the path to reach their hearts starts by creating a compelling sense of brand desire and finding the most authentic way to connect with them. 


The emergence in the industry of new cosmetics players along with a massive direct to consumers strategy have led to the creation of a highly competitive environment in which brands face difficulties to stand out. To remain relevant, the relationship with the consumer needs to be deeper, brands have to put their core values forward and show what they are truly made of. 


The real challenge is: how do you get the ‘authenticity’ message across? By creating a glocal environment. Led with the global brand image and desire and adjust the communication messages and ecosystem to be locally relevant across different client generations. 


When you’re a brand with over 100 million followers, you have an unequalled opportunity to share valuable ideas and statements. The brand adapts constantly to our client’s new behavior and expectations. The new role of marketing is not just about exceptional product and traditional advertising, it’s about creating the most desirable brand experience through every touchpoint- making sure that people understand the brand, connect with it, by sharing stories that are authentic and exclusive across channels, on-line and off-line. 


Can you share some insights about the post-pandemic period and the key challenges you are facing?

 

The pandemic has been a powerful accelerator of on-line consumption, with at least 25% of business being made on-line right now, and by a younger audience. We are now looking at the situation through a different prism asking ourselves: How can Dior stay connected to this young generation post-pandemic? And how can we develop a long, deep, emotional brand connection in this ongoing virtual world while continue to elevate our brand desirability? 


We also have to keep in mind that not every medium is right from one purpose to another. As a brand, you need to connect with people where they are and in a way that is relevant for the medium. 


For instance, a big post-pandemic change that matters is that sound/music is back on phones. Until 12 months ago, most people looked at their mobiles on silent mode. Since Covid, and mostly thanks to the explosion of Tik Tok globally, auditive immersion has been reintroduced in our way of life.


And this is great news for beauty, which is all about superior sensoriality. All these elements—music, podcasts, video—help you to immerse into a complete universe. Last year, Dior made a podcast about picking roses in the South of France for Miss Dior, and a whopper 86,000 people listened to it! This is exactly the daily connection you want to have. Marketing is no longer about invasive advertising, it’s about making your brand a conversational friend to our clients, and making people want to spend time with us, because they love us, trust us and adhere to our values. We are doing that by exposing the “behind the scenes” of our superior product craftsmanship and savoir faire, showing our exceptional gardens through the eyes of our artists and artisans, highlighting the ideas and motivations of the products as opposed to just focusing on the looks, bringing thus more dimension, and most of all a way deeper meaning.

 

You spoke about the young audience. What are the expectations of the younger generations and what does it mean for Parfums Christian Dior?

 

The young generation is showing us that the dream factor has evolved. We are discovering new codes of beauty and luxury thanks to them. For a growing number of young consumers, their aspiration is less about owning more than it is to express their best selves and buy goods that make them belong to a relevant point of view. By the way it is also true for non-millennials. That is why #beautyasalegacy is so dear to me, it encapsulates our sustainability approach. Data shows that one out of two beauty buyers is likely to turn away from brands that do not commit to answering global challenges today such as climate, gender equality, etc. Our leadership on our markets has to be backed by a solid leadership in sustainability, to grow the relevance of the Dior brand. 


I believe the Dior brand has a transformational role to play in two areas notably: in culture and in innovation. In culture, through the brand posture, the products, the content it shares, Dior can update perceptions of beauty, to make it more bold, progressive, and inclusive. This is what we are doing when encouraging women to #chinup (see below) as well as when we are launching 75 shades of FOREVER foundation so 100% of women can find their skin tone and get a product that highlights their genuine beauty.  


And of course, we can have a great impact through our innovations: it is about further strengthening eco-design, for example by accelerating the adoption of refills, that can have a lower weight of packaging / unit and a lower water and carbon footprint, with our iconic fragrance lines such as Sauvage which refill was launched end 2020. 
Sustainability is a journey, so we have to stay as passionate as humble.

Another key topic for the next generation is about diversity and inclusion. Could you please tell us more about the commitment of Parfums Christian Dior?

 

At Dior, we believe in and fight for our love for women since day one. In 1947, Christian Dior created the iconic Miss Dior out of this sincere affection. Today, his legacy lives on through DIOR STANDS WITH WOMEN, a female-led education and empowerment initiative.

This was the first time we decided to advocate for a cause by promoting a value instead of marketing a product. But the authenticity of the campaign carried us forward. Our videos were a massive hit and not because we said ‘Dior J’adore’, but because we said, “Dior is a house of powerful, strong women, who are proud of their achievements. Completely different women reunited by their own unique expression of the Triumphant Femininity and Empowerment that J’adore symbolised since its creation.” The relevance of the campaign rested on a principle of inclusivity, pride, community sharing and authenticity in their unfiltered messages to their “sisterhood”, a value to which you can relate instantly. And through this, we reached communities that we’d never touched before. This is not a marketing story but a meaningful long-term inspirational goal and brand commitment.

 

Any last words?


Ads and campaigns are not just for beautifying products anymore, but also for bringing awareness towards actions and communities. Purpose, meaning, and connection are some of the most desirable qualities in the eyes of today’s consumers.

 

To be relevant further down the line, we must connect with them. It can be through a talent or ambassador, because of our storytelling campaigns but most of all through our brand values expressed differently across the different pillars and axis. 
Today our job is to make sure that J’adore, Sauvage and Rouge Dior become cross generational and cross cultural, like pop icon. Our mission and passion is to keep our icons relevant every day and always extremely desirable across generations and countries. 
This is our challenge, this is the future of marketing.
